{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17510059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17510059"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:23:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:23:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11486"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11486","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11486"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.29,0.47,0.06,0.01,0.17]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4117"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106440"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4117","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4117"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11486"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88896"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1027"},{"type":"tags","id":"3101"},{"type":"tags","id":"3109"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"11691"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5072"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5125"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5644"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16677"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42609"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106440","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106440"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner. She was diagnosed with major depression several months ago after experiencing depressed mood, anhedonia and diurnal mood variation. At the time, she was commenced on fluoxetine, and had since increased her dose twice. Today she has returned to the practice reporting little improvement in her symptoms. It is decided that another antidepressant will be trialled.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most important consideration when switching from fluoxetine to another antidepressant?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Withdrawal symptoms","Serotonin toxicity","Inefficacy of antidepressants in this patient","Dependence on antidepressants","Using an antidepressant from a different class"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis question requires knowledge of commonly used SSRI, fluoxetine. The correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0027serotonin toxicity\u0027. \u003C/strong\u003EThis is because of the washout period of fluoxetine. Fluoxetine is an SSRI with an extended half life of up to 7 days. Thus, when switching from fluoxetine to another psychotropic medication, it is important to consider that there will be a \u0027washout period\u0027 during which fluoxetine is being cleared by the body. The risk associated with introducing a new psychotropic medication during this time is that levels of serotonin may become toxic, and thus cause serotonin syndrome in the patient. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Ewithdrawal symptoms\u003C/strong\u003E from sudden cessation of antidepressants is an important consideration, these are much rarer in antidepressants with long half-lives, including fluoxetine. Antidepressants with short half-lives including venlafaxine and paroxetine are more likely to cause withdrawal symptoms if ceased suddenly. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInefficacy of antidepressants in this patient\u003C/strong\u003E is the incorrect answer, as this patient has only tried one antidepressant. It is reported that 2/3rds of patients do not respond to the first antidepressant trialed. It is therefore very unlikely that antidepressants are ineffective, rather that fluoxetine is an ineffective drug in this patient. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAntidepressants are not known to cause dependence or addiction and thus \u003Cstrong\u003Edependence on psychiatric medications \u003C/strong\u003Eis not the correct answer. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe option of \u003Cstrong\u003Eusing an antidepressant from a different class\u003C/strong\u003E is the incorrect option. Although fluoxetine has been ineffective in improving this patients\u0027 symptoms, this does not mean that all antidepressants of the SSRI class will be ineffective. There is no evidence that changing to an antidepressant within the same class is less efficacious than switching to another class of antidepressant.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fluoxetine is an SSRI with a long half-life","The \u0027washout period\u0027 must be considered when switching between antidepressants, particularly in those with an extended half life","Serotonin toxicity may occur if antidepressants are not changed carefully"],"references":["Keks N, Hope J, Keogh S. Switching and stopping antidepressants. Aust Prescr. 2006 June;39(3);76-83."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88896"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11486"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88896","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88896"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-19T20:24:58+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-19T20:24:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4117"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106440"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","sy